name: 4-methylbenzeneboronic acid

On the other hand, the boronic acid group (B(OH)2) significantly increases the melting point. Boronic acids can form strong intermolecular hydrogen bonds which can drastically increase melting points, sometimes by more than +200°C compared to the base molecule. Considering these effects cumulatively but noting the substantial contribution of the boronic acid functionality, we may predict a significant increase.
